<Author>PeanutDotJU
<Content>Feeling hot, hot, hot!! We stayed at this hotel for two nights as part of an Archer's tour of Eastern European Cities. On arriving at the hotel it was obvious that it had been converted from a block of flats but was not necessarily unattractive. The rooms were adequately decorated, the only problem being that it was 35 degrees outside and there was no air conditioning at all making it very uncomforable to sleep. It was too noisy to leave the windows open and in any case no air was getting through. The breakfast was ok mainly typical continental. The bar was very nice with pleasant, friendly staff. There is a Lidl supermarket directly opposite the hotel and this may come in handy if you aren't very mobile or keen on walking as there aren't many bars or restaurants in the surrounding area. There is a U-Bahn station approximately a mile away which has a direct line to Alexanderplatz where there are many bars and restaurants (Escados Steakhouse being our favourite!). Overall it is manageable for two nights but can leave you feeling tired due to a lack of sleep and a lot of walking. 
