<Author>WNNX
<Content>The Communist Lifestyle All Over Again You will definitely feel that you are in East Germany when you venture to this property. It is so far from anything that it detracts from any positives the property may have. It took a 5 minute cab ride (6 Euros) just to get to the Metro/S-Bahn. On top of that it takes a good 30 minutes by Metro to get anywhere worthwhile.The hotel was spartan - no alarm clock, no coffee, not even washcloths. The staff was pleasant enough and they did try to accommodate needs.There was a bar in the lobby that was dingy and LOUD on a Saturday night when all the Poles, Italians and Dutch would kariocke to their hearts content.Overall, this hotel is just not worth it. 
