<Author>A TripAdvisor Member
<Content>Hot, basic and in the middle of nowhere I had the misfortune to room here during the World Cup, as all city centre hotels had been booked out, and we had to pay 275 Euros a night to stay here. It is a about 5 kilometres from the Mitte of Berlin, but is located in the middle of a former Eastern Bloc housing estate and industrial area. The rooms were spartan, but clean, but facilities were poor. Despite outside temperatures in excess of 35 degrees celcius there was no air conditioning, nor even a fan. The room was very noisy and smelt of smoke, despite being a non smoking room. The pillows and duvet seemed to be made of a man-made polyester style material making for a very sweaty and unpleasant sleeping experience. 
