<Author>A TripAdvisor Member
<Content>Tourist class transit camp I had the professional misfortune to stay at this hotel three times in 2002 while working as a driver guide for a british touring holiday company. The rooms are fine, if a little unexciting. The bar is okay but as you would expect, quite expensive. For those guests who wish to use Berlins extensive U  S Bahn network, you have to take a fifteen minute walk to the nearest U Bahn station. MEALS in this hotel are a DISASTER ZONE. What starts as a well stocked buffet is quickly cleared by the first group of guests and because the buffet is too small, the staff can never keep up with demand. The food quality is also questionable at times, menus are also often repeated from night to night. My advice is to eat out, its far better than joining the hotel bun fight every morning and evening. 
